Git API by LNET Technologies
Git Shell by LNET Technologies

Usage (API):

    git.get(author,repository,branch,path,saveName)
        'git.get()' is an API to retrieve a Github file from the specified destination.
            author: Owner of the repository
            repository: project
            branch: which branch you want to take from
            saveName: where to save the file

        'git.view()' is an API to simply VIEW the specified file. It is NOT saved!
            author: Owner of the repository
            repository: project
            branch: which branch you want to take from
            saveName: where to save the file

Usage (Shell):
    
    git [get/view] [author] [repository] [branch] [path] {file-name}